# ISO/IEC 17025 Alignment Statement
# --------------------------------
# This file defines technical responsibility, authorization, and change-control
# ownership for software components supporting laboratory operations.
#
# Alignment to ISO/IEC 17025:2017
# - Clause 6.2  : Personnel competence and authorization
# - Clause 6.3  : Infrastructure and controlled environments
# - Clause 6.4  : Equipment, software, and systems control
# - Clause 7.11 : Control of data, information management, and integrity
# - Clause 8.3  : Control of management system documents
# - Clause 8.5  : Actions to address risks and opportunities
#
# Governance Principles
# ---------------------
# - All changes must be attributable to a responsible individual
# - High-risk components require explicit technical authorization
# - The last matching rule takes precedence
# - Code Owners must approve pull requests affecting owned components
###############################################################################

